# MySQL Query Performance

Keep Prisma queries fast. Slow or N+1 queries must be fixed before marking work complete.

## Query rules

- Use `select` to fetch only needed fields — avoid loading `LongText`/`Text` unless required
- Never run database queries inside loops — batch with `findMany` + `in`, `include`, or `$transaction`
- List endpoints must use `take`/`skip` or cursor pagination — no unbounded `findMany`
- Prefer one query with `include` over N separate `findUnique` calls

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// BAD — N+1: fetches all groups N times
groups.map(async (g) => canAccessGroup(userId, g.id, levelId))

// GOOD — one fetch for groups + one batch fetch for progress
const progress = await prisma.userProgress.findMany({
  where: { userId, groupId: { in: groupIds } },
})
```

## Before claiming done

- Check for N+1 patterns in new or changed query code
- For raw/complex SQL, recommend `EXPLAIN` to verify index usage
- Large models (`Material.content`, `Question.question`): exclude from list queries

